# Push and deploy after changes

When you finish a coherent set of code changes in this repo:

1. Run tests or typechecks relevant to the edited areas when practical.
2. Commit with a concise message focused on why the change was made.
3. Push to `origin/main`.
4. Deploy by running `./scripts/update-remote-deployment.local.sh` from the repo root.

Do not skip push/deploy unless the user explicitly says not to for that turn, or there are no committed code changes to ship.

Do not commit build artifacts (for example `*.tsbuildinfo`).

If deploy fails, report the failure and fix blockers before ending the turn when possible.
